# Commit messages

Every commit message must:

1. **Start with one emoji** that reflects the kind of change (see table below).
2. Use a **short description in English**, imperative mood (e.g. “Add…”, “Fix…”, “Update…”).
3. Optional: add a blank line and a longer body in English if needed.

**Format (single line):**

```text
<emoji> <English description>
```

**Examples:**

```text
✨ Add shiny toggle to Pokemon card
🐛 Fix hunt list not updating on language change
♻️ Refactor PokeApiService cache keys
🌐 Add missing ES labels for settings screen
📝 Update AGENTS.md with commit conventions
```

**Emoji guide (pick one that best matches the change):**

| Emoji | Use for |
|-------|---------|
| ✨ | New feature |
| 🐛 | Bug fix |
| ♻️ | Refactor (no user-visible change) |
| 🎨 | UI / styling only |
| 🌐 | Internationalization / translations |
| ⚡️ | Performance |
| ✅ | Tests |
| 📝 | Documentation only |
| 🔧 | Config, tooling, chores |
| 🔒 | Security |

Do **not** write the main description in Spanish; English only for the commit line and body.
